:true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":13588,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/04\/15\/talaq-worst-of-halal\/","url_meta":{"origin":33612,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Talaq: Worst of permissible matters is divorce","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 15, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe most hateful of lawful matters to Allah is divorce.\u201d Source: Sunan Ab\u012b D\u0101w\u016bd 2172 Grade: Sahih\u00a0(authentic) according to Al-Suyuti \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0652\u063a\u064e\u0636\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33863,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/01\/01\/khula-warning-divorce\/","url_meta":{"origin":33612,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Khula: Warning against initiating frivolous divorce","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 1, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Thawban reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cIf a woman asks her husband for a divorce without a strong reason, the fragrance of Paradise becomes forbidden for her.\u201d Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 2226 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Arna\u2019ut \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u062b\u064e\u0648\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33879,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/01\/06\/prophet-angered-by-triple-talaq\/","url_meta":{"origin":33612,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Divorce: The Prophet is angered by triple talaq","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 6, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Mahmud ibn Labid reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, was informed about a man who pronounced divorce to his wife three times at once. The Prophet stood in anger and he said, \u201cDo they play with the Book of Allah while I am among you?\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33889,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/01\/07\/umar-talaq-triple-divorce\/","url_meta":{"origin":33612,"position":3},"title":"Umar on Talaq: The Caliph punishes men who triple divorce","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 7, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas reported: Whenever a man was brought to Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, who had divorced his wife three times in one sitting, he would flog his back. Source: Sharh\u0323 Ma\u02bba\u0304ni\u0304 al-\u0100tha\u0304r 4488 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Ibn Hajar \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0633\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064f \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33873,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/01\/06\/divorce-triple-talaq\/","url_meta":{"origin":33612,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Divorce: Triple talaq in the time of the Prophet, Abu Bakr, and Umar","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 6, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: Triple divorce in the time of the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, Abu Bakr, and two years of the Caliphate of Umar was considered to be only one revocable divorce. Umar ibn al-Khattab said, \u201cVerily, the people have become hasty in a matter\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":2845,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/04\/10\/allah-forgives-mistakes-coercion\/","url_meta":{"origin":33612,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Pardon: Allah forgives honest mistakes, coerced sins","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 10, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Dharr reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, Allah has pardoned my nation for their mistakes, their forgetfulness, and what they are coerced into doing.\u201d Source: Sunan\u00a0Ibn Ma\u0304jah 2043 Grade: Sahih\u00a0(authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0630\u064e\u0631\u064d\u0651 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/33612","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=33612"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/33612\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=33612"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=33612"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=33612"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}